I'd like to be able to inject options in my game object.
## Actual behavior:

``` as3
public function Startup() 
{
    _starling = new Starling(Game, stage);
    _starling.start();
}
```
## Proposition:

``` as3
public function Startup() 
{
    var options:Object = {};
    _starling = new Starling(Game, stage, options);
    // options could then for example be avalaible in the Game instance as _options attribute.
    _starling.start();
}
```
## pros:
- load ressource in the "Startup.as" file (seem logic to load resources before instanciating application)
- Previous would also avoid most classname conflict (and/or the related horrible hacks).
- Permit to have several instance of the same game with different configuration
## Cons:

None of my knowlege, it's an optional attribute, and will still be compatible with game using older version of core.Starling.
